sometimes even dependencies have bugs, and if you then dont&#39; want to risk update even minor version dependency, then you have a sort of problem if your forced version contains a new commit with a  bug but version not increased - happens, so one has to delete the global cache manually selectively or update a single one - if it&#39;s not an issue - all dependencies, but sometimes the buggy is the newest one version with that specific number, and it needs to be waited for the nearest coming bugfix of the vendors library/dependency, therefore that cleaning of global cache manually is a must rather than waiting for a vendor hotfix, youre bug might be already discovered few months after the project went live

